From 42cd7faf1dcb38ad9353213186f9797e009cb430 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 12:18:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Delete Unit and Delete Part buttons - the backend
 protection already existed, nothing called it

Both DELETE /units/:id and DELETE /parts/:id already existed and were
already properly protected (blocked with a clear error if the unit/
part has any in-progress, pending-verification, or completed work) -
but grep confirmed zero frontend usage of either endpoint anywhere in
the app. The safety net existed; there was genuinely no door to walk
through it.

Unit detail page: "Delete Unit" in the header (unit:manage), confirms
before deleting, navigates back to Production Calendar on success.
Each part in the Parts list gets its own delete button (part:manage),
confirms before deleting, doesn't touch the rest of the page.

Planner Dashboard: each part chip on a unit card gets a small X to
remove it - this is genuinely the most likely place a mistake actually
happens (dragging the wrong part type onto a unit), so it gets its own
direct undo right where the mistake occurs, not just on the unit
detail page.

Both soft-delete (deletedAt), consistent with how deletion already
works everywhere else in this app - recoverable, not a hard delete.
